OL,3,CBoy, 14, seriously injured after fall
OL,4,Con Welsh mountain
OL,6,FA rescue helicopter located him on the
OL,7,Fwest face of Tryfan at about 8pm.
OL,9,FLowering a rescuer on a winch to reach
OL,10,Fthe casualty, Mr Lloyd explained: "He
OL,11,Fidentified that the boy was still
OL,12,Falive and conscious."
OL,14,FHe was found in a steep, craggy area
OL,15,Fwhich had recently had a major
OL,16,Frockfall.
OL,18,FThe boy was put onto a stretcher at
OL,19,Fabout 10.30pm and airlifted down to
OL,20,Fthe base.
